D%5C%22Young%20man%20wearing%20headphones%20working%20on%20computer%20at%20startup%20office.%20Young%20IT%20professional%20working%20at%20coworking%20office%20with%20people%20working%20at%20back.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65731ad67a3c8094d5daeea5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20future%20workplace%20could%20see%20more%20of%20a%20focus%20on%20employee%20mental%20health%20and%20wellbeing.%3Cp%3EGetty%2FLuis%20Alvarez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20expanding%20beyond%20rideshare%20and%20delivery%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20IT%20field%20worker%20in%20Virginia%20told%20Business%20Insider%20how%20he%20uses%20two%20platforms%20to%20find%20gigs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20worker%20said%20that%20he%C2%A0%26quot%3Bconstantly%26quot%3B%20thinks%20about%20finding%20a%20regular%20job%2C%20though%20he%20likes%20the%20flexibility.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20an%20IT%20field%20worker%20in%20Virginia%20who%20finds%20gigs%20on%20WorkMarket%20and%20Field%20Nation%2C%20two%20platforms%20for%20IT%20contractors.%20The%20contractor%20asked%20that%20Business%20Insider%20not%20publish%20his%20name%20for%20fear%20of%20retaliation%20from%20WorkMarket%20and%20Field%20Nation%2C%20but%20BI%20has%20verified%20his%20identity%20and%20employment.%20The%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20contacted%20by%20a%20company%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20seemed%20to%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-job-satisfaction-unhappy-work-salary-promotion-loyalty-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20opening%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%202%20%C2%BD%20years%20ago.%20I%20had%20quit%20my%20full-time%20job%20because%20it%20felt%20like%20time%20to%20move%20on%2C%20but%20I%20made%20a%20terrible%20mistake%3A%20I%20left%20before%20I%20had%20another%20position.%20One%20day%2C%20I%20got%20a%20call%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20for%20traveling%20IT%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20just%20jumped%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverything%20looked%20like%20this%20was%20just%20a%20normal%20hiring%20process.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EThey%20were%20looking%20for%20somebody%20to%20do%20some%20computer%20networking%20for%20them.%20They%20had%20me%20go%20through%20the%20steps%20to%20sign%20up%20through%20WorkMarket%2C%20which%20seemed%20like%20the%20company's%20platform%20for%20managing%20workflow.%20They%20asked%20all%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-things-to-lie-about-in-an-interview-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20job%20interview%20questions%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20do%20you%20see%20yourself%20in%20five%20years%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20after%20that%20call%20ended%20and%20I%20really%20started%20looking%20at%20WorkMarket%20that%20I%20realized%20the%20job%20was%20a%20contract%20role.%20There%20were%20jobs%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20companies%20on%20WorkMarket.%20It's%20gig%20work%2C%20essentially%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-make-money-driving-for-doordash-gig-economy-rewards-program-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20IT%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20now%20worked%20for%20lots%20of%20different%20companies%20through%20WorkMarket%20and%20Field%20Nation%2C%20a%20similar%20platform.%20Companies%20hire%20me%20to%20do%20jobs%20on%20their%20behalf%2C%20usually%20at%20other%20companies%20that%20are%20their%20clients.%20My%20day-to-day%20can%20be%20anything%20from%20fixing%20printers%20to%20a%20hard-drive%20swap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20apps%20usually%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20tell%20the%20client%20companies%20that%20you've%20been%20recruited%20through%20Field%20Nation.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20they%20want%20us%20to%20say%20we're%20here%20%26quot%3Bon%20behalf%20of%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20that%20hired%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20out%20mostly%20doing%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20which%20is%20network%20administration.%20But%20on%20these%20platforms%2C%20it's%20been%20difficult%20to%20be%20successful%20just%20doing%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20WorkMarket%20and%20Field%20Nation%20charge%20their%20gig%20workers%20fees.%20Of%20the%20two%2C%20Field%20Nation's%20are%20significantly%20higher%20%E2%80%94%20about%2015%25%20%E2%80%94%20than%20WorkMarket%2C%20where%20they're%20about%2010%25.%20And%20the%20fees%20are%20on%20everything%2C%20not%20just%20earnings.%20If%20I%20do%20a%20job%20and%20I%20run%20200%20feet%20of%20cable%2C%20I%20request%20the%20cost%20of%20that%20back%2C%20and%20Field%20Nation%20takes%2015%25%20of%20that.%20Even%20if%20it's%20a%20mileage%20reimbursement%2C%20they%20take%20a%20cut%20of%20the%20total%20cost%20before%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20baked%20that%20into%20my%20costs.%20I%20add%20in%20that%20extra%2015%25%20on%20top%20of%20whatever%20those%20are.%20But%20some%20companies%20I%20work%20for%20aren't%20happy%20with%20that%20and%20push%20back.%20There%20have%20been%20times%20when%20they've%20refused%20to%20pay%20the%20extra%20amount%2C%20and%20I've%20taken%20the%20hit%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20contractor%2C%20you%20also%20get%20rated%20on%20these%20platforms%20by%20the%20companies%20you%20work%20for%20based%20on%20the%20job%20you%20do%2C%20whether%20you%20showed%20up%20on%20time%20and%20other%20stuff.%20Both%20of%20them%20put%20it%20front%20and%20center%20that%20if%20your%20ratings%20get%20too%20low%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20we%20can%20rate%20the%20companies%20we%20work%20for%2C%20but%20obviously%2C%20they%20can%20see%20what%20we%20say.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20contractor%20ratings%20of%20companies%2C%20you'll%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20five-star%20reviews.%20If%20you%20give%20a%20company%20one%20star%2C%20they're%20just%20not%20going%20to%20send%20you%20work%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20so%20difficult%20to%20decide%20if%20this%20is%20better%20than%20a%20regular%2C%209-to-5%20job.%20The%20main%20benefit%20is%20that%20I%20have%20contacts%20at%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20companies%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20if%20I%20had%20just%20been%20working%20at%20one.%20The%20actual%20money%20I%20make%20ends%20up%20being%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20I%20would%20get%20at%20a%20regular%20job%2C%20though%20I'm%20not%20paid%20for%20the%20time%20that%20I'm%20sitting%20at%20home%2C%20looking%20for%20my%20next%20gig%2C%20and%20setting%20up%20my%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20the%20freedom.%20I%20can%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20work%20this%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20I%20won't%20take%20jobs%20and%20go%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-take-vacation-work-remotely-monthly-without-telling-my-boss-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etake%20a%20vacation.%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20with%20the%20fees%20and%20extra%20costs%2C%20how%20am%20I%20going%20to%20save%20up%20to%20take%20a%20vacation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDo%20I%20think%20about%20getting%20a%20regular%20job%20again%3F%20Constantly.%20But%20how%20would%20I%3F%20Work%20dried%20up%20during%20the%20holidays%2C%20so%20I%20started%20looking%20for%20something%20that%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20work%20from%20home.%20It%20was%20so%20difficult%20to%20find%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20jobs%20also%20ask%20for%20references.%20But%20on%20these%20platforms%2C%20everybody%20I%20speak%20to%20works%20for%20another%20company%2C%20and%20I'm%20just%20a%20contractor.%20It%20kind%20of%20traps%20you.%20I%20can%20pull%20up%20the%20apps%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20got%20five%20stars%2C%20and%20I%20was%20on%20time%2098%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20there's%20nowhere%20for%20that%20on%20an%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnless%20I'm%20lucky%20enough%20to%20sit%20in%20front%20of%20a%20person%20who's%20hiring%20to%20explain%20my%20background%2C%20my%20application%20will%20be%20automatically%20eliminated.%20I%20really%20wish%20I%20would've%20thought%20about%20that%202%20%C2%BD%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20ADP%2C%20which%20owns%20WorkMarket%2C%20told%20BI%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20contractor%20leverages%20the%20WorkMarket%20platform%2C%20they%20are%20engaging%20with%20a%20business%20to%20complete%20an%20assignment%20for%20the%20business%20or%20the%20business'%20end-client.%20When%20working%20with%20the%20end%20client%2C%20we%20recommend%20contractors%20note%20that%20they%20are%20completing%20the%20assignment%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20business%20that%20engaged%20them%2C%20as%20that%20is%20who%20they%20are%20completing%20the%20work%20on%20behalf%20of.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BContractors%20are%20welcome%20to%20reference%20the%20WorkMarket%20by%20ADP%20platform%2C%20however%2C%20WorkMarket%20does%20not%20employ%20the%20contractor%20and%20does%20not%20provide%20any%20directions%20to%20the%20contractor%20on%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20project.%20Our%20platform%20is%20used%20to%20connect%20the%20company%20offering%20the%20project%20with%20the%20worker%20that%20will%20complete%20it.%20The%20company's%20end-client%20does%20not%20engage%20with%20WorkMarket%2C%20so%20referencing%20the%20platform%20may%20cause%20some%20confusion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20spokesperson%20also%20said%20that%20contractors%20and%20companies%20can%20rate%20each%20other%20on%20factors%20%26quot%3Bincluding%20overall%20satisfaction%2C%20quality%2C%20professionalism%2C%20and%20communication%2C%20but%20WorkMarket%20does%20not%20have%20any%20involvement%20in%20making%20or%20using%20the%20rating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Field%20Nation%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20fee%20model%20is%20transparent%2C%20offering%20a%20variety%20of%20features%20and%20services%20that%20reduce%20the%20administrative%20burden%20that%20comes%20with%20being%20an%20independent%20contractor%20or%20business%20owner%2C%20namely%20finding%20clients%20and%20administrative%20overhead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20do%20gig%20work%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-work-apps-tech-work-want-full-time-role-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708252321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ccd288f533b039a8837811%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-work-apps-tech-work-want-full-time-role-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gig%20work%20is%20expanding%2C%20but%20this%20IT%20contractor%20who%20finds%20work%20on%20Field%20Nation%20and%20WorkMarket%20says%20he%20thinks%20%26quot%3Bconstantly%26quot%3B%20about%20a%20full-time%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-work-apps-tech-work-want-full-time-role-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mati%20Diop%20Merges%20Fact%20With%20Fantasy%20In%20Berlin%20Doc%20%E2%80%98Dahomey%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708252244000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FMixCollage-17-Feb-2024-03-02-PM-7350.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariet