umenting%20the%20crises%20that%20the%20nation%20went%20through.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20legacy%20that%20was%20lost%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20remarks%20one%20winter%20morning%20while%20sipping%20coffee%20and%20sitting%20at%20his%20makeshift%20office%20in%20one%20of%20the%20by-lanes%20of%20Old%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20started%20in%20the%20crisis%20and%20ended%20in%20the%20crisis%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20laments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20a%20historical%20magazine%20that%20first%20came%20out%20in%201925%2C%20before%20India%20became%20independent.%20It%20was%20started%20by%20Khawaja%20Hassan%20Nizami%2C%20a%20poet%20and%20historian%20who%20was%20actively%20involved%20in%20politics%20and%20had%20a%20rivalry%20with%20Diwan%20Singh%20Maftoon%2C%20another%20famous%20Urdu%20journalist%2C%20over%20the%20princely%20states%20in%20the%20British%20Raj.%20It%E2%80%99s%20coming%20into%20being%20was%20political%2C%20as%20it%20was%20started%20to%20support%20the%20political%20stance%20of%20Khawaja%20Hassan%20Nizami.%20After%20the%20rivalry%20ended%2C%20Nizami%20handed%20over%20the%20magazine%20to%20Mufti%20Shoukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20who%20then%20became%20the%20editor%20and%20managed%20the%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20took%20over%20as%20editor%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20its%20content%20was%20filled%20with%20political%20articles.%20Against%20the%20odds%2C%20to%20have%20advertisements%20and%20business%2C%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20started%20the%20film%20section%20in%20the%20magazine%20that%20covered%20film%20controversies%2C%20gossip%20about%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20and%20offered%20criticism%20on%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsif%20Fehmi%20remembers%20his%20father%20telling%20him%20that%20then-famous%20Jaddanbai%20Hussain%2C%20singer%2C%20dancer%2C%20and%20actress%20of%20Indian%20cinema%2C%20and%20famous%20actress%20Saira%20Banu%2C%20visited%20the%3Cem%3E%20Din%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20office.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20various%20Hindi%20film%20personalities%20who%20visited%20the%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20office%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20was%20a%20fear%20in%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20of%20negative%20coverage%20by%20the%20magazine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%201935%20to%201947%2C%20films%20dominated%20the%20magazine.%20As%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20partitioned%20in%201947%2C%20the%20magazine%20shut%20down%20for%20the%20first%20time%20%E2%80%9Cbecause%20of%20the%20circumstances%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20migrated%20to%20Lahore%20and%20opened%20a%20shop%20in%20Anarkali%20Bazaar.%20Right%20after%20migrating%20to%20the%20other%20side%2C%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20not%20the%20right%20country%20for%20him%20and%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20chose%20Delhi%20over%20Lahore%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%201947%2C%20as%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20partitioned%20and%20the%20socio-political%20scenario%20of%20the%20country%20changed%2C%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20came%20out%20with%20a%20new%20version.%20The%20film%20section%2C%20for%20which%20the%20magazine%20was%20known%20previously%2C%20was%20skipped.%20Instead%2C%20Islamic%20history%2C%20Tafseer-e-Quran%20and%20historic%20incidents%20of%20the%20Islamic%20world%20found%20their%20way%20into%20the%20magazine.%20Now%20the%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20focus%20shifted%20to%20historical%2C%20political%20and%20mainly%20religious%20events%20in%20the%20country%20and%20the%20world.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20societal%20need%20of%20the%20time%20to%20include%20Islamic%20history%20and%20carry%20Tafseer-e-Quran%20in%20parts%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20famous%20%E2%80%98Raftar-e-Zamana%E2%80%99%20column%20for%20the%20editorial%20largely%20focused%20on%20violence%20against%20minorities%20after%201947.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20used%20his%20pen%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20speaking%20truth%20to%20power.%20His%20editorials%20were%20incisively%20political%2C%20busting%20myths%20that%20were%20used%20to%20target%20minorities%20and%20create%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20hostility.%20These%20editorials%20are%20preserved%20by%20his%20son%20Asif%20Fehmi%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EMufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20Hayaat%20va%20Khidmaat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EMufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20Life%20and%20Contributions%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20which%20he%20dedicated%20to%20his%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201959%2C%20in%20the%20January%20issue%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20the%20editorial%20focused%20on%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Dhulia%20riots.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20condemned%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20violence%E2%80%9D%20and%20wrote%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20stop%20the%20riots%20and%20not%20being%20able%20to%20create%20a%20peaceful%20environment%20for%20the%20minorities%20to%20exist%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20editorial%2C%20in%20the%20May%20issue%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9Criots%20are%20prevalent%20in%20the%20country%20every%20now%20and%20then%20after%201947.%20It%20has%20become%20our%20daily%20reality.%E2%80%9D%20He%20even%20targeted%20newspapers%20like%20%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20propagating%20hate%20against%20Muslims.%20In%20the%20August%20editorial%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20he%20went%20on%20to%20write%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccommunal%20disharmony%20is%20not%20the%20issue%20of%20Muslims%20but%20of%20unity%2C%20of%20democracy%2C%20of%20nationhood%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20a%20month%20passes%20without%20riots%20happening%20in%20India.%20Secularism%20has%20failed%3B%20it%20has%20been%20shredded%20to%20pieces%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201963%20editorial%20of%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%20accused%20%3Cem%3EAmrit%20Bazaar%20Patrika%2C%20Anand%20Bazaar%20Patrika%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20%E2%80%9Cinciting%20communal%20disharmony%20and%20peddling%20hate%20against%20Muslims%E2%80%9D.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20suggest%20that%20%E2%80%9Cif%20we%20need%20to%20fight%20against%20communalism%2C%20all%20minorities%20have%20to%20unite.%20Jan%20Sangh%20is%20the%20enemy%20of%20each%20minority%20in%20India.%20India%20will%20be%20destroyed%20by%20communalism.%20All%20parties%20need%20to%20unite%20to%20fight%20against%20Jan%20Sangh.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD-300x96.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD-1024x328.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697712%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOld%20covers%20of%20%E2%80%98Din%20Dunia%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%2C%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%20also%20accused%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20fear%20in%20the%20country%20for%20minorities%E2%80%9D%20and%20prophesied%20that%20in%20the%20near%20future%20they%20will%20work%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccreation%20of%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20and%20will%20rename%20the%20historical%20buildings%20ascribed%20to%20Muslims%2C%20an%20example%20being%20Taj%20Mahal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20slammed%20the%20Congress%20for%20not%20providing%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%20and%20other%20minorities%20the%20space%20for%20equity%20in%20the%20social%2C%20political%2C%20and%20economic%20spectrum%2C%20which%20thus%20helps%20the%20RSS%20in%20further%20propagating%20their%20mission%20of%20Hindu%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20with%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20the%20Urdu%20language%20was%20also%20partitioned.%20The%20decline%20in%20the%20readership%20of%20Urdu%20has%20always%20been%20a%20focus%20for%3Cem%3E%20Din%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%2C%20in%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%20that%20focused%20on%20the%20Urdu%20language%2C%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9CCinderella%E2%80%9D%20because%20%E2%80%9Cit%20awaits%20the%20magic%20touch%20that%20can%20free%20it%20from%20its%20minority%20status%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20condemned%20the%201986%20Education%20Policy%2C%20in%20which%20%E2%80%9Cno%20attention%20was%20paid%20to%20Urdu%E2%80%9D.%20He%20writes%20in%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%20that%20%E2%80%9CUrdu%20was%20born%20here%3B%20it%20grew%20up%20here.%20More%20than%20the%20Muslims%2C%20the%20Hindus%20also%20grew%20up%20reading%20and%20writing%20in%20this%20language.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Raftar-e-Zamana%E2%80%99%20was%20a%20much-awaited%20column%20that%20attracted%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20from%20readers.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20used%20to%20wait%20for%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says.%20It%20dealt%20with%20the%20most%20sensitive%20and%20critical%20issues%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20currently%20under%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%20long%20ago%20criticised%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%20written%20in%20February%201990%2C%20when%20the%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20was%20under%20the%20rule%20of%20Governor%20Jagmohan.%20He%20mentioned%20in%20the%20editorial%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20unlucky%20state%20of%20India%20that%20sinks%20into%20Governor%20Raj%20every%20now%20and%20then%E2%80%9D.%20While%20praising%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccommunal%20harmony%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20he%20also%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9Cparadise%20on%20earth%20has%20been%20turned%20into%20hell%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnobody%20is%20serious%20enough%20to%20solve%20this%20issue%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20termed%20it%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmain%20cause%20of%20conflict%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20year%201992%2C%20when%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20demolished%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Ayodhya%2C%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20took%20a%20strong%20stance.%20It%E2%80%99s%20editorial%20condemned%20the%20%E2%80%9CRSS%2C%20VHP%2C%20and%20Rath%20Yatra%E2%80%9D%20and%20predicted%20that%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cworse%20situation%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CWhatever%20is%20happening%20in%20Ayodhya%20is%20not%20sudden.%20It%20is%20well-planned%E2%80%A6%5Band%20the%5D%20mandate%20is%20given%20to%20them%20by%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Asif%20Fehmi%2C%20journalism%20happened%20abruptly.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20who%20had%20managed%20and%20edited%20the%20magazine%2C%20died%20in%201993%20after%20being%20ill%20for%20two%20years.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20no%20one%20to%20look%20after%20the%20magazine.%20It%20was%20our%20legacy.%20We%20were%20associated%20with%20the%20magazine.%20We%20are%20still%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98Din%20Dunia-wale%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says%2C%20as%20he%20remembers%20the%20time%20when%20he%20took%20over%20as%20editor%20of%20the%20magazine.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20my%20father%20died%2C%20I%20was%20already%20running%20the%20magazine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManaging%20the%20magazine%20was%20a%20tough%20job%20for%20young%20Asif%20Fehmi.%20His%20education%20was%20English-based%2C%20and%20he%20had%20only%20read%20Urdu%20as%20a%20subsidiary%20subject%20in%20college.%20Before%20that%2C%20Asif%20was%20involved%20in%20clerical%20work%20for%20the%20magazine%20while%20his%20father%20was%20alive%20and%20was%20given%20a%20stipend%20for%20it.%20That%20is%20how%20Asif%20entered%20the%20legacy%20that%20his%20father%20had%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPublishing%20a%20magazine%20is%20a%20job%20where%20you%20require%20teamwork.%20But%20here%20it%20was%20done%20single-handedly%20by%20me.%20I%20managed%20the%20whole%20thing%3A%20proofreading%2C%20content%20gathering%20and%20publishing%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20two%20people%20were%20working%20under%20him%20%E2%80%93%20one%20managing%20the%20clerical%20work%20and%20the%20other%20helping%20with%20the%20editorial%20work.%20The%20magazine%20was%20supported%20by%20the%20publication%20of%20books%20alongside%20it.%20Financial%20viability%20was%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20that%20hindered%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20magazine%20and%20later%20shut%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%20pursued%20the%20struggle%20of%20keeping%20the%20%E2%80%9Clegacy%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20family%20alive%2C%20which%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cservice%20to%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20up%20until%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20the%20country%20in%202020.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20offices%20of%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20seized%20by%20the%20Municipal%20Corporation.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20don%E2%80%99t%20permit%20any%20industrial%20work%20in%20the%20walled%20city%2C%20not%20even%20printing%20presses%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20readership%20of%20Urdu%20has%20declined%20massively.%20Digitisation%20has%20affected%20the%20readership%20of%20Urdu%20magazines%20and%20newspapers.%20%E2%80%9CTimes%20have%20changed.%20Urdu%20lovers%20don%E2%80%99t%20prefer%20to%20read%20Urdu%20newspapers.%20There%20was%20a%20time%20when%20people%E2%80%99s%20only%20source%20of%20information%20was%20newspapers%20and%20magazines.%20Nowadays%2C%20it%20is%20the%20internet%20and%20social%20media%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20four%20years%20later%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%20has%20only%20memories%20of%20his%20lost%20legacy.%20He%20has%20an%20archive%20that%20has%20the%20print%20issues%20of%20the%20magazine%20collected%20in%20a%20large%20file.%20He%20misses%20being%20in%20the%20office.%20His%20days%20are%20spent%20only%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20reviving%20the%20magazine.%20Asif%20Fehmi%20aims%20to%20bring%20the%20magazine%20back%20in%20digital%20form%20and%20in%20print%20quarterly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20very%20sure%20about%20the%20digitisation%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20but%20I%20am%20positive%20about%20it.%20Will%20I%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it%3F%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20There%20is%20uncertainty.%20And%20I%20lack%20experience%20in%20the%20digital%20field%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20it%20will%20always%20have%20a%20place%20in%20my%20memory.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMir%20Umar%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708251373000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154308%2FDin-Dunia.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrom-politics-to-movies-and-back-again-the-story-of-urdu-magazine-din-dunia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20magazine%20stopped%20publishing%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020.%20Its%20last%20editor%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%2C%20remembers%20the%20magazines%20trajectory%20%E2%80%93%20and%20hopes%20to%20give%20it%20another%20life%20soon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrom-politics-to-movies-and-back-again-the-story-of-urdu-magazine-din-dunia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%2081-year-old%20explains%20her%20simple%20solution%20to%20make%20sure%20loneliness%20doesn't%20become%20'a%20way%20of%20life'%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20she%20thinks%20stands%20in%20the%20way%20of%20forming%20connections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Patricia%20Backlund%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb9f3c6fcb546d2d4f1b4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222432%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPatricia%20Backlund%2C%2081%2C%20started%20weekly%20%26quot%3Bmingles%26quot%3B%20in%20her%20community%20to%20combat%20loneliness.%3Cp%3EPatricia%20Backlund%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPatricia%20Backlund%2C%2081%2C%20combats%20loneliness%20by%20organizing%20a%20weekly%20%26quot%3BFriday%20mingle%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20community.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20efforts%20reflect%20a%20larger%2C%20global%20initiative%20to%20address%20loneliness%20and%20promote%20social%20connection.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20impacts%20of%20loneliness%20can%20be%20especially%20harmful%20for%20older%20adults%20who%20might%20not%20have%20many%20relationships.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPatricia%20Backlund%2C%2081%2C%20wouldn't%20describe%20herself%20as%20lonely%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20knows%20how%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20become%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Backlund%20and%20her%20husband%20moved%20to%20Gig%20Harbor%2C%20Washington%2C%20six%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20initially%20chose%20a%20home%20in%20a%2055-plus%20community.%20However%2C%20she%20later%20decided%20that%20she%20wanted%20a%20more%20independent%20setting%2C%20so%20she%20moved%20to%20a%20nearby%20community%20that%20was%20still%20being%20built%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20none%20of%20the%20residents%20knew%20each%20other%20very%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBacklund%20decided%20to%20change%20that%20by%20organizing%20a%20weekly%20meetup%20that%20she%20started%20in%20June%20and%20now%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3BFriday%20mingle%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20about%2020%20to%2030%20people%20in%20the%20community%20meet%20in%20the%20pavilion%20to%20simply%20talk%20to%20one%20another%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20I%20tell%20the%20group%2C%20especially%20the%20new%20people%20that%20come%2C%20is%20that%20the%20reason%20we%20do%20this%20is%20to%20get%20to%20know%20each%20other%2C%20to%20be%20supportive%20of%20each%20other%2C%20to%20be%20available%20to%20help%20each%20other%20when%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20Backlund%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20some%20of%20these%20people%20don't%20have%20children%20nearby.%20Some%20of%20them%20don't%20have%20children%20at%20all%2C%20so%20your%20neighbor%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20closest%20person%20that%20you%20can%20go%20to%20and%20get%20help%20if%20you%20need%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221554%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Patricia%20Backlund%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbcc0f94aa8ee8e84aeb9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221166%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPatricia%20Backlund.%20%3Cp%3EPatricia%20Backlund%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20has%20been%20a%20success%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20in%20forming%20friendships%20but%20lifelong%20relationships.%20Backlund%20said%20that%20two%20of%20the%20members%20announced%20they%20had%20fallen%20in%20love%2C%20and%20that%20wouldn't%20have%20happened%20would%20it%20not%20have%20been%20for%20the%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20acknowledged%20that%20for%20other%20older%20adults%2C%20going%20to%20the%20mingle%20and%20introducing%20themselves%20to%20strangers%20might%20not%20be%20so%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20loneliness%20is%20sometimes%20based%20in%20fear%2C%26quot%3B%20Backlund%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20that%20you%20might%20learn%20to%20live%20with%2C%20and%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20fear%20or%20not%20being%20able%20to%20really%20carry%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20another%20person%2C%20it%20becomes%20a%20way%20of%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20of%20all%20ages%20have%20been%20battling%20loneliness%2C%20and%20the%20pandemic%20exacerbated%20the%20issue%20over%20recent%20years.%20It%20led%20US%20Surgeon%20General%20Vivek%20Murthy%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hhs.gov%2Fabout%2Fnews%2F2023%2F05%2F03%2Fnew-surgeon-general-advisory-raises-alarm-about-devastating-impact-epidemic-loneliness-isolation-united-states.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeclare%20it%20an%20epidemic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20launched%20a%20plan%20to%20ensure%20Americans%20don't%20succumb%20to%20the%20impacts%20of%20loneliness%2C%20which%20include%20increased%20risk%20of%20heart%20disease%20and%20for%20older%20adults%2C%20increased%20risk%20of%20dementia%20and%20premature%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20once%20people%20come%20to%20understand%20that%20loneliness%20is%20also%20common%20and%20consequential%2C%20it's%20giving%20people%20the%20urgency%2C%20motivation%20and%20permission%20they%20need%20to%20pursue%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20Murthy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F12%2F18%2Fsurgeon-general-tools-loneliness-00131734%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20Politico%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBacklund%20knows%20the%20urgency%20of%20addressing%20loneliness%20and%20hopes%20that%20more%20people%20start%20taking%20the%20matter%20into%20their%20own%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20is%20unpredictable%20and%20things%20come%20up%20that%20we%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20tell%20somebody%20about%20what's%20going%20on%20and%20get%20some%20input%2C%20get%20wisdom%20from%20each%20other%2C%20especially%20if%20you've%20been%20through%20similar%20kinds%20of%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20Backlund%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'You%20have%20to%20take%20the%20initiative'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Global%20Initiative%20on%20Loneliness%20and%20Connection%20%E2%80%94%20a%20group%20of%20organizations%20around%20the%20world%20working%20to%20address%20loneliness%20%E2%80%94%20wrote%20in%20its%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gilc.global%2F_files%2Fugd%2F410bdf_62e236db3a7146cd9f2654877a87dbc6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposition%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20being%20%26quot%3Bsocially%20connected%20is%20recognized%20as%20a%20fundamental%20human%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20greater%20social%20connection%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20positively%20influence%20a%20range%20of%20mental%2C%20physical%2C%20and%20cognitive%20health%20outcomes%2C%20with%20the%20strongest%20evidence%20showing%20that%20being%20more%20socially%20connected%20reduces%20risk%20for%20premature%20all-cause%20mortality%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Backlund%20said%20she%20feels%20so%20strongly%20about%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20those%20who%20might%20be%20isolated%2C%20or%20hesitant%20to%20make%20new%20social%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20take%20the%20initiative%20to%20really%20reach%20out%20to%20your%20neighbors%20or%20your%20community%2C%20and%20if%20you%20don't%20do%20it%2C%20nobody's%20going%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20loneliness%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20people%20don't%20want%20to%20take%20the%20initiative%20to%20reach%20out%20and%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20let's%20do%20this%2C%20let's%20go%20here.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20has%20previously%20spoken%20to%20other%20older%20adults%20who%20found%20solutions%20of%20their%20own%20to%20prevent%20becoming%20lonely.%20One%2075-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-crisis-retiree-how-to-achieve-happiness-budget-retirement-seniors-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20a%20group%20at%20his%20senior%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20people%20can%20gather%20and%20chat%20once%20a%20week%2C%20and%20he%20said%20it%20sparked%20meaningful%20connections%20that%20many%20of%20the%20attendees%20lacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%2070-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-villages-loneliness-making-friends-in-retirement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecided%20to%20join%20a%20%26quot%3Bsenior%20village%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20community%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20but%20offers%20resources%20and%20activities%20to%20help%20connect%20its%20members.%20And%20a%2063-year-old%20who%20hasn't%20yet%20retired%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-solve-loneliness-older-adult-planning-retirement-biggest-fear-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethinking%20proactively%20about%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ensure%20that%20loneliness%20doesn't%20catch%20up%20to%20him%20when%20he's%20no%20longer%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20not%20careful%20at%20this%20stage%20of%20my%20life%2C%20my%20life%20expectancy%20will%20diminish%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20overall%20well-being%20is%20definitely%20tied%20to%20my%20family%20and%20my%20relationships%2C%20and%20that's%20where%20the%20currency%20is.%20It's%20about%20the%20simple%20act%20and%20the%20necessity%20of%20being%20engaged.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20efforts%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20at%20a%20federal%20level.%20Reps.%20Mike%20Flood%20and%20David%20Trone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflood.house.gov%2Fmedia%2Fpress-releases%2Fcongressmen-flood-trone-introduce-bipartisan-bill-measure-scope-loneliness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Improving%20Measurements%20for%20Loneliness%20and%20Isolation%20Act%20in%20November%2C%20aimed%20at%20bringing%20stakeholders%20together%20to%20increase%20social%20connections.%20And%20Sens.%20Chris%20Murphy%20and%20Bob%20Casey%20in%20December%20%3Ca%20href%3D