20earnings%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20one%20figure%20is%20sure%20to%20stand%20out%20as%20having%20gotten%20noticeably%20smaller%20last%20year%3A%20the%20number%20of%20US%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20quietly%20reduced%20its%20fleet%20by%20more%20than%20100%20locations%20between%20January%20and%20August%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20company's%20investor%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20reported%20a%20combined%204%2C717%20supercenters%2C%20discount%20stores%2C%20and%20smaller%20format%20locations%20at%20the%20start%20of%20its%20fiscal%20year%2C%20and%20declined%20to%204%2C616%20in%20the%20span%20of%20two%20quarters.%20No%20closures%20were%20reported%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20and%20any%20changes%20since%20November%20will%20be%20reflected%20when%20the%20company%20files%20its%20annual%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20declined%20to%20provide%20additional%20details%20about%20the%20closures%20to%20Business%20Insider%20before%20the%20SEC's%20pre-earnings%20quiet%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20most%20of%20last%20year%2C%20BI%20tracked%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-store-closings-2023-full-list%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20Walmart%20closures%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20US%20through%20federally%20required%20layoff%20notices%20filed%20with%20state%20workforce%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20combined%2022%20supercenters%2C%20stores%2C%20and%20neighborhood%20markets%20that%20fell%20off%20the%20company's%20tally%20during%20the%20year%2C%20spokespeople%20said%20the%20locations'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-store-closings-openings-2024-full-list%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20performance%20was%20not%20meeting%20expectations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20so%20many%20store%20closures%20flew%20under%20the%20radar%20has%20to%20do%20with%20their%20size%3A%2079%20locations%20were%20extremely%20tiny