2%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107793167%2Cimgsize-28326.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fhas-kartik-aaryans-aashiqui-3-title-changed-to-tu-aashiqui-hai%2Farticleshow%2F107792513.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107792513.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAfter%20wrapping%20up%20work%20on%20'Chandu%20Champion'%2C%20Kartik%20Aaryan%20is%20gearing%20up%20for%20his%20next%20film%20'Aashiqui%203'.%20According%20to%20the%20latest%20buzz%2C%20the%20film%20could%20possibly%20get%20a%20new%20title%20-%20'Tu%20Aashiqui%20Hai'%20-%20as%20it%20will%20reportedly%20pay%20homage%20to%20the%20classic%201981%20film%20'Basera'.%20The%20makers%20are%20reportedly%20still%20looking%20out%20for%20a%20female%20lead%20to%20star%20in%20the%20film.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Becoming%20Human%3A%20Forged%20by%20Fire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18113620%2F1620px-Bandipur_fires_2019.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20third%20article%20in%20a%20series%20about%20the%20Earth-system%20%E2%80%93%20how%20our%20planet%20has%20shaped%20us%20as%20human%20beings%2C%20and%20how%20we%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20have%20shaped%20it.%20Read%20the%20series%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fearths-changing-climate%5C%22%3EPart%201%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-planetary-perspective%5C%22%3EPart%202%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFire%20looms%20large%20in%20the%20ancient%20myths%20of%20many%20peoples%20around%20the%20world.%20Interestingly%2C%20most%20of%20these%20old%20stories%20share%20a%20common%20motif%2C%20in%20which%20fire%20was%20withheld%20from%20humankind%E2%80%94either%20by%20gods%20or%20by%20some%20other%20being%E2%80%94until%20humans%20finally%20acquired%20it%20only%20through%20an%20act%20of%20theft%2C%20violence%2C%20or%20other%20ignoble%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20tale%20from%20ancient%20Greece%2C%20the%20god%20Prometheus%20steals%20fire%20from%20his%20fellow%20gods%20to%20share%20it%20with%20humans%3B%20for%20this%20transgression%2C%20the%20other%20gods%20condemn%20him%20to%20endure%20an%20eternity%20of%20torture.%20The%20Polynesian%20demigod%2C%20Maui%20the%20trickster%2C%20ventures%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20world%20to%20retrieve%20fire%20from%20his%20grandmother%20Pele%2C%20the%20god%20of%20fire%2C%20by%20taking%20her%20burning%20fingernails%20one%20by%20one%E2%80%94only%20to%20churlishly%20extinguish%20each%20one%3B%20Pele%20finally%20grows%20so%20angry%20with%20him%20that%20she%20sends%20fire%20chasing%20after%20him%20into%20the%20human%20world.%20In%20one%20Din%C3%A9%20(Navajo)%20story%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fteachersinstitute.yale.edu%2Fcurriculum%2Funits%2F1998%2F2%2F98.02.02%2F5%5C%22%3Efire%20god%3C%2Fa%3E%20hoards%20fire%20for%20himself%2C%20using%20it%20only%20to%20destroy%20things%2C%20until%20trickster%20Coyote%20steals%20some%20and%20gives%20it%20to%20humans.%20Among%20different%20Australian%20Aboriginal%20peoples%2C%20the%20origin%20of%20fire%20is%20placed%20with%20various%20animals%2C%20or%20sometimes%20human%20women%2C%20from%20whom%20it%20is%20forcibly%20taken%20through%20violence%20or%20trickery%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20then%20distributed%20among%20the%20trees%20of%20the%20land%2C%20from%20where%20anyone%20can%20recover%20it.%20The%20ancient%20Vedic%20and%20Zoroastrian%20traditions%20are%20a%20bit%20different%2C%20but%20the%20fire%20god%E2%80%94Agni%20or%20Atar%E2%80%94is%20both%20devourer%20and%20protector.%20As%20the%20light%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vyasaonline.com%2Fencyclopedia%2Fagni%2F%5C%22%3Eknowledge%20and%20acculturation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academia.edu%2F39553500%2FProto_Indo_European_Fire_Theft_Myth%5C%22%3EAgni%20too%20once%20hid%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20humans%2C%20before%20serving%20as%20an%20intermediary%20between%20humans%20and%20the%20gods%20of%20the%20Vedic%20pantheon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20288px)%2085vw%2C%20288px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22288%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20stories%20from%20every%20quarter%20of%20the%20planet%20engage%20with%20the%20mystery%20and%20power%20of%20fire%20in%20ways%20that%20we%20of%20industrial%20civilisation%20do%20not.%20They%20imagine%20fire%20as%20being%20of%20divine%20origin%20or%20imbued%20with%20some%20property%20fundamentally%20tied%20to%20our%20very%20humanity%2C%20the%20world%20we%20inhabit%2C%20or%20divinity.%20Without%20it%2C%20our%20human%20world%20is%20incomplete.%20Yet%20an%20ambivalence%20too%20surrounds%20fire%2C%20either%20through%20explicit%20acknowledgement%20of%20its%20dual%20nature%20as%20both%20benefactor%20and%20destroyer%20or%20an%20implicit%20association%20of%20it%20with%20an%20act%20of%20transgression%20or%20moral%20corruption.%20But%20we%20need%20it%2C%20the%20stories%20tell%20us%3B%20its%20power%20to%20cook%20food%20and%20to%20keep%20us%20warm%20enables%20our%20human%20existence.%20Our%20evolutionary%20story%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20very%20deeply%20bound%20up%20with%20fire.%20And%20though%20no%20living%20society%20can%20possibly%20retain%20a%20true%20memory%20of%20the%20origins%20of%20a%20bond%20forged%20millions%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20remarkable%20that%20a%20mythic%20awareness%20of%20its%20centrality%20to%20human%20societies%2C%20its%20powers%20and%20its%20dangers%2C%20remains%20alive%20among%20peoples%20who%20retain%20their%20cultural%20connection%20with%20a%20non-industrialised%20worldview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDirect%20human%20connection%20to%20fire%20began%20as%20global%20temperatures%20were%20dropping%20into%20the%20Pleistocene%20ice%20age.%20Our%20early%20hominid%20ancestors%20in%20Africa%20had%20left%20the%20forest%20canopies%2C%20where%20they%E2%80%99d%20enjoyed%20a%20diet%20of%20raw%20leaves%20and%20fruit%2C%20seeds%20and%20insects%2C%20to%20explore%20new%20ways%20of%20life%20on%20the%20expanding%20open%20savannas.%20Their%20grassland%20lifestyles%20favored%20evolution%20toward%20bipedalism%2C%20along%20with%20dextrous%20minds%20and%20hands%20able%20to%20sharpen%20rocks%20into%20cutting%20implements.%20They%20must%20have%20learned%20they%20could%20glean%20good%20food%20from%20the%20charred%20leavings%20of%20forest%20fires.%20This%20accidental%20cooking%20rendered%20some%20foods%20easier%20to%20eat%20and%20digest%2C%20enabling%20these%20hominids%20to%20enjoy%20nutritious%20foods%20they%20might%20not%20have%20eaten%20before%2C%20like%20the%20calorifically%20dense%20tubers%20and%20corms%20that%20grew%20underground.%20This%20meant%20their%20bodies%20could%20receive%20more%20nutrition%20from%20food%20while%20expending%20less%20energy%20in%20processing%20and%20digesting%20it%2C%20because%20fire%20effectively%20did%20some%20of%20that%20processing%20and%20digesting%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chem.fsu.edu%2Fchemlab%2Fchm1020c%2FLecture%252525207%2F01.php%5C%22%3EFire%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D_GLb0s-FfZU%5C%22%3Eunique%20to%20Earth%20as%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself.%20It%20erupts%20when%20substances%20made%20mostly%20of%20carbon%20and%20hydrogen%E2%80%94fuels%2C%20like%20wood%20or%20oil%2C%20ultimately%20created%20by%20some%20living%20thing%E2%80%94are%20combined%20with%20ambient%20oxygen%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reagent.co.uk%2Fblog%2Fchemistry-of-fire%2F%5C%22%3Erunaway%20oxidative%20chemical%20reaction%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20converts%20them%20primarily%20into%20carbon-dioxide%20and%20water.%20The%20heat%20given%20off%20by%20this%20reaction%20can%20keep%20us%20warm%20in%20the%20cold%20or%20drive%20reactions%20in%20other%20substances%2C%20like%20in%20the%20food%20we%20eat.%20High%20heat%20changes%20the%20properties%20of%20our%20food%20by%20neutralising%20poisons%20it%20contained%20in%20its%20raw%20state%20(tubers%20and%20beans%20can%20be%20toxic%20before%20cooking)%2C%20softening%20its%20hard%20parts%2C%20killing%20any%20pathogens%20within%20it%2C%20altering%20the%20structures%20of%20its%20proteins%2C%20and%20releasing%20nutrients%20for%20easier%20absorption%20by%20our%20guts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndaman%20Islanders%20once%20had%20many%20living%20stories%20about%20the%20origins%20of%20fire.%20According%20to%20English%20anthropologist%20A.R.%20Radcliffe-Brown%2C%20who%20attempted%20to%20record%20them%20as%20they%20were%20fast%20disappearing%20under%20colonisation%2C%20several%20stories%20credited%20an%20ancestral%20matriarch%20for%20inventing%20fire.%20Some%20say%20she%20struck%20a%20red%20stone%20against%20a%20pearl%20shell%20(which%20also%20stood%20for%20lightening)%2C%20then%20fed%20the%20fire%20with%20wood%20and%20fell%20asleep.%20While%20she%20slept%2C%20Sir%20Dove%20stole%20this%20fire%20for%20himself.%20He%20later%20distributed%20fire%20to%20every%20village.%20It%E2%80%99s%20uncanny%20how%20this%20story%20echoes%20others%20from%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20energy%20we%20take%20from%20fire%20is%20%3Cem%3Eextra-somatic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20meaning%20it%20comes%20from%20outside%20of%20our%20bodies%2C%20beyond%20the%20calories%20we%20ingest%20in%20our%20food.%20Thus%2C%20controlling%20fire%20allows%20us%20to%20%E2%80%98steal%E2%80%99%20the%20energy%20released%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fuel%20and%20add%20some%20of%20it%20to%20the%20energy%20we%20get%20from%20the%20food%20itself%2C%20effectively%20increasing%20the%20amount%20of%20energy%20we%20use%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%94both%20directly%2C%20in%20the%20energy%20of%20cooking%2C%20and%20indirectly%2C%20by%20enabling%20us%20to%20extract%20more%20food%20energy%20from%20the%20same%20environment%20through%20an%20expanded%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20take%20this%20for%20granted%2C%20but%20this%20is%20the%20magic%20of%20cooking.%20And%20it%20marked%20a%20fundamental%20transition%20in%20how%20our%20kind%20taps%20into%20the%20resources%20available%20in%20our%20ecosystems.%20It%20gave%20us%20a%20larger%20portion%20of%20energy%20from%20an%20environment%20we%20share%20with%20other%20creatures%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20depend%20entirely%20on%20energy%20from%20the%20food%20they%20eat%20to%20maintain%20their%20life%20functions.%20At%20some%20point%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2019%2Fnov%2F21%2Fwildfire-prescribed-burns-california-native-americans%5C%22%3Enobody%20knows%20when%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94human%20communities%20also%20began%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.org%2Fen-us%2Fmagazine%2Fmagazine-articles%2Findigenous-controlled-burns-california%2F%5C%22%3Epractice%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbandipur-mudumalay-wayanad-controlled-forest-fire-biomass%5C%22%3Econtrolled%20burns%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fsubjects%2Ffire%2Findigenous-fire-practices-shape-our-land.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520goal%2520of%2520this%2520prescribed%2Cpreceded%2520by%2520a%2520traditional%2520ceremony.%5C%22%3Eshape%20and%20maintain%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucdavis.edu%2Fnews%2Fcultural-burning-illuminated%5C%22%3Eecosystems%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.universityofcalifornia.edu%2Fnews%2Fhow-indigenous-practice-good-fire-can-help-our-forests-thrive%5C%22%3Ewidely%20beneficial%3C%2Fa%3E%20ways%2C%20perhaps%20not%20so%20unlike%20the%20way%20other%20animals%20are%20known%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findigenousknowledge.unimelb.edu.au%2Fcurriculum%2Fthemes%2Ffire%5C%22%3Eshape%20their%20ecosystems%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20building%20dams%20(beavers)%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20or%20maintaining%20waterholes%20(elephants).%20This%20became%20another%20way%20that%20humans%20actively%20co-created%20enriched%20environments%2C%20alongside%20other%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20living%20system%20uses%20(consumes)%20more%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20it%20grows%3B%20for%20early%20humans%2C%20their%20increased%20consumption%20of%20biomass%E2%80%94as%20fuel%20to%20make%20fire%20and%20as%20food%E2%80%94would%20have%20caused%20an%20increase%20in%20their%20population%20size.%20The%20local%20ecosystem%20had%20to%20adjust%2C%20accommodating%20more%20%3Cem%3EHomo%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20fewer%20of%20something%20else%E2%80%94most%20noticeably%2C%20perhaps%2C%20other%20directly%20competing%20species%2C%20like%20similar%20hominids%20who%20did%20not%20use%20fire.%20The%20use%20of%20fire%20increased%20the%20%3Cem%3Ecarrying%20capacity%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20landscape%20for%20%3Cem%3EH.%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94that%20is%2C%20the%20land%20could%20support%20larger%20populations%20of%20them%20living%20this%20way%20of%20life%20effectively%20forever%2C%20or%20at%20least%20until%20something%20else%20changed%20their%20environment.%20Perhaps%20no%20other%20animals%20have%20made%20such%20intensive%20and%20crafty%20use%20of%20extra-somatic%20energy%20as%20humans%E2%80%94nor%20become%20so%20existentially%20dependent%20upon%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20all.%20All%20the%20ease%20our%20ancestors%20gained%20by%20cooking%20favored%20the%20evolution%20of%20new%20body%20forms%20with%20smaller%20guts%20and%20teeth%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbigthink.com%2Fthe-present%2Finventions-fire%2F%5C%22%3Elarger%20brains%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Before%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20Pleistocene%20ice%20age%2C%20our%20ancestors%20controlled%20fire%20well%20enough%20to%20build%20cooking%20hearths.%20This%20suggests%20that%2C%20rather%20than%20eating%20on%20the%20spot%20whatever%20each%20one%20collected%20or%20killed%2C%20as%20most%20primates%20do%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faustralian.museum%2Flearn%2Fscience%2Fhuman-evolution%2Fhominid-and-hominin-whats-the-difference%2F%5C%22%3Ehominins%3C%2Fa%3E%20carried%20their%20day%E2%80%99s%20bounty%20back%20to%20their%20camp%2C%20threw%20it%20onto%20the%20fire%2C%20and%20then%20shared%20it%20with%20their%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20indigenous%20peoples%20around%20the%20world%2C%20some%20Adivasis%20once%20maintained%20their%20forest%20ecosystems%20by%20setting%20controlled%20fires.%20Such%20regular%20burns%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.survivalinternational.org%2Fnews%2F11939%5C%22%3Eprevented%20wildfires%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20during%20British%20Colonial%20times%2C%20when%20forests%20became%20widely%20perceived%20primarily%20as%20a%20source%20of%20timber%20and%20profit%2C%20the%20Adivasis%E2%80%99%20controlled%20burns%20were%20stopped.%20This%20is%20one%20reason%20why%20wildfires%20have%20become%20a%20growing%20threat%20in%20India%2C%20more%20so%20under%20the%20rising%20heat%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitting%20around%20the%20hearth%2C%20distributing%20food%2C%20contesting%20over%20what%20was%20fair%20and%20who%20owed%20what%20to%20whom%2C%20suffering%20harassment%20by%20the%20greedy%20meanies%E2%80%94or%20collectively%20harassing%20them%20in%20retribution%E2%80%94social%20pressures%20favored%20evolution%20toward%20increasing%20capacities%20to%20understand%20and%20utter%20vocalisations%20that%20coded%20for%20more%20complex%20and%20nuanced%20information.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20enriched%20imaginative%20powers%20that%20could%20project%20one%20person%20into%20another%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%2C%20able%20to%20visualize%20and%20contemplate%20encounters%20and%20experiences%20known%20only%20through%20gestural%20and%20vocal%20communication.%20Our%20hominin%20ancestors%20had%20already%20been%20teaching%20each%20other%20how%20to%20fashion%20tools%2C%20how%20to%20tend%20fire%2C%20perhaps%20even%20how%20to%20locate%20the%20best%20tubers%20or%20caches%20of%20nuts%20or%20honey.%20Maybe%2C%20in%20exchanging%20information%20about%20their%20environment%20by%20recounting%20their%20day%E2%80%99s%20exploits%2C%20they%20began%20to%20tell%20stories%20in%20language%20increasingly%20rich%20enough%20to%20build%20worlds%2C%20to%20articulate%20beliefs%20and%20rules%20about%20how%20to%20live%2C%20to%20profess%20their%20love%20or%20to%20complain%20about%20the%20resident%20bully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20while%20these%20earliest%20humans%20were%20developing%20cooking%20technologies%20that%20transformed%20their%20bodies%2C%20they%20were%20also%20growing%20into%20highly%20social%2C%20cooperative%20animals%20capable%20of%20teaching%20and%20learning%20from%20one%20another%20about%20their%20material%20and%20social%20worlds.%20Over%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20generations%20they%20accumulated%20this%20knowledge%2C%20passed%20it%20down%20from%20elders%20to%20youths%2C%20recounted%20it%20in%20tales%20told%20around%20the%20fire%2C%20listening%20to%20the%20sounds%20of%20the%20night%2C%20gazing%20up%20at%20a%20milky%20profusion%20of%20stars.%20From%20this%20they%20would%20weave%20threads%20upon%20threads%20of%20human%20stories%20into%20tapestries%20of%20meaning%2C%20eventually%20gathering%20these%20together%20and%20binding%20them%2C%20layer%20over%20layer%2C%20into%20all%20enveloping%20edifices%20of%20%3Cem%3Ehuman%20culture%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94an%20immersive%20environment%20of%20stories%2C%20a%20universe%20of%20interconnected%20notions%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20shared%20delusion%20that%20models%20for%20each%20community%20their%20shared%20meanings%20of%20life%2C%20how%20the%20cosmos%20works%2C%20what%20has%20value%2C%20what%20is%20their%20rightful%20place%20in%20the%20world%2C%20what%20possible%20futures%20lie%20before%20them%2C%20and%20much%20else%20besides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20culture%20is%20an%20awe-inspiring%20phenomenon%20that%20has%20long%20forged%20meaning%20and%20purpose%20in%20conversation%20with%20our%20deep%20awareness%20of%20the%20planet%E2%80%99s%20biophysical%20reality.%20However%E2%80%94as%20future%20essays%20in%20this%20series%20will%20describe%E2%80%94in%20modern%2C%20industrial%20societies%2C%20the%20tether%20between%20culture%20and%20biophysical%20reality%20has%20become%20increasingly%20frayed%3B%20our%20modern%20culture%20has%20now%20become%20a%20self-referential%20bubble%2C%20adrift%20from%20our%20planet%E2%80%99s%20own%20life%20and%20rhythms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20early%20ancestors%20first%20learned%20to%20control%20fire%2C%20the%20ecological%20shift%20was%20apparently%20gradual.%20It%20remained%20sustainable%20for%20well%20over%20a%20million%20years%2C%20even%20as%20it%20increased%20human%20populations%20enough%20to%20spread%20out%20of%20Africa%20and%20establish%20themselves%20across%20ice-age%20Eurasia.%20Nevertheless%2C%20when%20humans%20entered%20those%20far-flung%20ecosystems%2C%20this%20would%20necessarily%20have%20destabilised%20them%20at%20first.%20It%20would%20have%20left%20them%20forever%20altered%20them%20forever%20by%20accommodating%20a%20new%20apex%20predator%E2%80%94human%20beings%E2%80%94on%20the%20local%20landscapes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20trove%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2666033423000266%5C%22%3Earchaic%20stone%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1040618220304754%5C%22%3Esites%20across%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20alongside%20a%20handful%20of%20early%20hominin%20fossils%20from%20the%20Narmada%20River%20basin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC378623%2F%5C%22%3Eand%20modern%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.wayne.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D2055%26context%3Dhumbiol%5C%22%3Egenetic%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20attest%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-020-14668-4%5C%22%3Econtinuous%20presence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fscience%2Fstone-tools-found-tamil-nadu-suggest-humans-left-africa-much-earlier%5C%22%3Emultiple%20human%20lineages%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20subcontinent%20since%20the%20dispersal%20of%20%3Cem%3E%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%20out%20of%20Africa.%20The%20oldest%20finds%2C%20unearthed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmart-news%2Fstone-tools-india-raise-questions-about-spread-ancient-technology-180968020%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DArchaeologists%2520at%2520the%2520Sharma%2520Center%2Cwith%2520the%2520Early%2520Stone%2520Age.%5C%22%3EAttirampakkam%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20simple%20stone%20tools%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2666033423000266%5C%22%3E1.5%20million%20years%20old%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20plausibility%20that%20different%20lineages%20intermixed%20over%20a%20thousand%20millennia%20suggests%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fscience%2Fstone-tools-found-tamil-nadu-suggest-humans-left-africa-much-earlier%5C%22%3Emajor%20crossroads%20for%20human%3C%2Fa%3E%20admixture%20and%20evolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20species%20that%20increases%20its%20number%20within%20an%20ecosystem%20ultimately%20changes%20the%20conditions%20for%20all%20other%20local%20species%2C%20because%20their%20enlarged%20presence%20changes%20the%20way%20that%20energy%20and%20materials%20flow%20through%20that%20ecosystem.%20But%20fluctuations%20of%20species%20within%20changing%20ecosystems%20are%20normal%20for%20living%20systems%2C%20which%20are%20never%20static.%20Disruptions%20and%20even%20occasional%20extinctions%20caused%20by%20the%20expansion%20of%20one%20species%20need%20not%20lead%20to%20total%20annihilation%20of%20ecosystems%20nor%20disintegration%20of%20the%20planet%E2%80%99s%20biogeochemical%20cycles.%20In%20fact%2C%20once%20an%20ecosystem%20establishes%20a%20new%20balance%20to%20accommodate%20a%20new%20species%2C%20it%20may%20ultimately%20become%20richer%20than%20it%20had%20been%20before.%20Such%20fluctuations%20are%20different%20from%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20large-scale%20ecosystem%20%3Cem%3Eannihilation%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20marks%20the%20Anthropocene%20and%20is%20only%20a%20recent%20development%2C%20not%20necessarily%20intrinsic%20to%20our%20human%20nature%20or%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20one%20has%20to%20wonder%20if%20the%20stories%20told%20by%20the%20first%20Australians%2C%20the%20Din%C3%A9%2C%20the%20Polynesians%2C%20and%20others%2C%20as%20they%20were%20expanding%20across%20the%20planet%20in%20their%20time%2C%20captured%20some%20unnamed%20awareness%20of%20the%20destabilization%20their%20presence%20brought%20to%20their%20new%20lands.%20Could%20that%20be%20one%20source%20of%20their%20stories%E2%80%99%20ambivalence%20about%20fire%3F%20Was%20it%20some%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20moral%20and%20existential%20dangers%20of%20mastering%20a%20force%20mightier%20than%20themselves%3F%20Of%20the%20disruptions%20they%20caused%20with%20its%20super-human%20power%3F%20The%20ancient%20stories%20may%20have%20reminded%20their%20audiences%20that%20wielding%20the%20power%20of%20fire%20entails%20responsibilities%2C%20obligating%20us%20into%20a%20system%20of%20mutual%20sharing%20and%20care%20for%20our%20environment%2C%20fundamentally%20tied%20to%20our%20own%20survival%E2%80%94a%20wisdom%20we%20have%20forgotten%20in%20our%20industrial%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20time%20I%E2%80%99ll%20look%20at%20the%20crucial%20role%20ice%20also%20plays%20in%20the%20human%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%3Cem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EOnly%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708241441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18113620%2F1620px-Bandipur_fires_2019.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-forged-by-fire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fire%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20as%20unique%20to%20Earth%20as%20life%20itself.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-forged-by-fire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Baloch%20labourer%20killed%20by%20Pakistan%20coast%20guard%2C%20activist%20urges%20action%20against%20forces%20disappearance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708241358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107793042%2Cimg