ship%20and%20was%20surrounded%20by%20sharks.%20He%20displayed%20remarkable%20composure%20despite%20significant%20bleeding%20and%20emphasized%20that%20sharks%20pose%20a%20threat%20only%20when%20they%20feel%20threatened%20themselves.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fakshay-kumars-near-death-experience-filming-dangerous-underwater-stunt-for-blue%2Farticleshow%2F107792215.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stagnant%20Job%20Rate%2C%20Worse%20for%20the%20Educated%3A%20IIM%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29174355%2F20240123_092445.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Researchers%20from%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Management%2C%20IIM%20Lucknow%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20Birla%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20and%20Science%20(BITS)%20Pilani%20and%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20for%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%2C%20have%20found%20%E2%80%9Ca%20stagnating%20employment%20growth%20rate%2C%20weakening%20employment%20elasticity%2C%20slow%20structural%20transformation%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fiim-study-points-to-structural-problems-in-indian-labour-market%2Farticle67857448.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520number%2520of%2520unemployed%2520people%2Cmarket%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520the%2520paper%2520said.%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20has%20reported%20on%20their%20findings%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Journal%20of%20Labour%20Economics%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CJobless%20growth%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20have%20used%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20Office%20(NSSO)%20Employment%20and%20Unemployment%20Survey%20and%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey.%20The%20have%20concluded%20that%20there%20was%20a%20surge%20in%20output%20growth%20and%20employment%20between%201987%E2%80%9388%20and%202004%E2%80%9305%2C%20followed%20by%20%E2%80%98jobless%20growth%E2%80%99%20from%202004%E2%80%9305%20to%202018%E2%80%9319%20and%20a%20very%20small%20%E2%80%9Crebound%E2%80%9D%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CApparently%2C%20economic%20growth%2C%20rather%20than%20creating%20more%20jobs%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20net%20labour%20displacement.%20Alongside%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20important%20to%20examine%20the%20quality%20and%20decency%20of%20jobs%2C%E2%80%9D%20Professor%20S.%20Tripati%20Rao%20of%20IIM%2C%20Lucknow%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%20In%202020%E2%80%9321%2C%20the%20total%20labour%20force%20in%20India%20was%20at%20556.1%20million.%20Of%20this%20a%20majority%20or%2054.9%25%20were%20self-employed%2C%20just%2022.8%25%20in%20regular%20employment%20and%20an%2022.3%25%20in%20casual%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-workforce-not-rising-quality-of-jobs-very-low-cmies-mahesh-vyas%5C%22%3Ereported%20on%20May%202%2C%202023%20on%20the%20crisis%20in%20jobs%20as%20well%20as%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mahesh%20Vyas%20of%20CMIE%20had%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs%20in%20India%20is%20very%20low.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20jobs%20pay%20poorly%20and%20are%20of%20informal%20arrangements%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sectors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20job%20data%20has%20been%20patchy%20and%20not%20revealed%20regularly%20of%20late.%20There%20are%20also%20serious%20questions%20about%20what%20it%20captures%20and%20is%20it%20reflects%20employment%20precarity%20at%20all.%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Fstatistics%2Fjob-quality.htm%5C%22%3EOECD%20uses%20three%20%E2%80%9Cobjective%20and%20measurable%20dimensions%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20to%20help%20quantify%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs%2C%20which%20Indian%20data%20still%20does%20not%20do.%20The%20three%20criteria%20are%2C%20earnings%20quality%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Ccaptures%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20earnings%20contribute%20to%20workers%E2%80%99%20well-being%20in%20terms%20of%20average%20earnings%20and%20their%20distribution%20across%20the%20workforce.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20The%20labour%20market%20security%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20working%20environment%20are%20the%20other%20two%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGender%20disparity%20worsens%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IIM%2FBITS%2FMinistry%20of%20Agriculture%20study%20has%20also%20found%20gender-based%20disparity%20in%20the%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20Rate%20(LFPR)%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20continues%20and%20worryingly%2C%20the%20decline%20of%20LFPR%20is%20higher%20for%20females%20than%20for%20males%20from%201983%20to%202020%E2%80%9321.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20overall%20female%20Work%20Force%20Participation%20Rate%20(WFPR)%20for%20those%20aged%2015%E2%80%9359%20in%202020%E2%80%9321%20stood%20at%2032.46%25%2C%20a%20full%2044.55%20percentage%20points%20below%20that%20of%20men.%20Further%2C%20the%20total%20percentage%20of%20male%20WFPR%20(81.10%25)%20in%20the%20same%20year%20for%20aged%2015%E2%80%9359%20years%20is%20more%20than%20twice%20the%20rate%20for%20female%20adults%20(33.79%25)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20study%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20much%20higher%20for%20highly%20educated%20Indians%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20India%20has%20been%20helping%20mediate%20between%20foreign%20governments%20like%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20more%20controversially%20in%20Israel%2C%20for%20providing%20semi-skilled%20and%20unskilled%20labour%20to%20those%20countries%2C%20signalling%20its%20inability%20to%20provide%20jobs%20in%20basic%20manufacturing%20industries%20in%20the%20country.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Ftaiwan-agrees-bring-indian-migrant-workers-ease-job-crunch-2024-02-16%2F%5C%22%3EMoU%20with%20Taiwan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20this%20respect%20was%20signed%20on%20February%2016%2C%202024.%20The%20jobs%20crisis%20in%20India%2C%20as%20per%20the%20BBC%E2%80%99s%20report%20last%20month%2C%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-68027582%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cdriving%20workers%20to%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20even%20before%20the%20war%20on%20Gaza%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20India%20had%20%E2%80%9Csigned%20an%20agreement%20in%20May%202023%20that%20would%20send%2042%2C000%20Indian%20construction%20and%20nursing%20workers%20to%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20comments%20by%20former%20Israeli%20foreign%20minister%20Eli%20Cohen%20in%20the%20Israeli%20Knesset%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fisrael-conducts-recruitment-drive-in-uttar-pradesh-haryana-as-bar-on-gaza-palestinians-workers-caused-labour-shortage-11706146837290.html%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20%3Cem%3EMint.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20prospects%20for%20employment%20do%20not%20improve%20with%20rising%20education%20levels%20and%20progressively%20get%20worse%2C%20also%20as%20per%20this%20study%2C%20suggesting%20a%20comprehensive%20failure%20to%20generate%20jobs%20across%20the%20board%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20India%20rises%20with%20education%20levels.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20illiterate%20and%20less%20educated%20class%20(below%20primary)%20was%200.57%25%20and%201.13%25%20respectively%20while%2C%20for%20the%20highly%20educated%20class%20(graduates%20and%20above)%2C%20it%20was%2014.73%25%20in%202020%E2%80%9321%20for%20the%20age%20group%2015%E2%80%9329%20years.%E2%80%9D%20This%20pattern%20can%20be%20seen%20across%20the%20years%2C%20as%20per%20the%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20recommends%20more%20attention%20to%20MNREGA%2C%20other%20poverty%20alleviation%20programmes%20and%20public%20works.%20It%20finds%20MNREGA%20to%20positively%20help%20with%20%E2%80%9Craising%20wages%20in%20rural%20areas%20by%205%25%2C%20increase%20in%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20among%20female%20workers%2C%20improvement%20in%20low-caste%20working%20bargaining%20power%2C%20increasing%20rural%20wage%20levels%2C%20and%20fall%20in%20reliance%20on%20high-caste%20employers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708238575000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29174355%2F20240123_092445.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fstagnant-job-rate-worse-for-the-educated-iim-study%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20study%20by%20IIM%2C%20BITS%20(Pilani)%20and%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%20finds%20that%20India%20is%20not%20generating%20enough%20jobs.%20The%20gender%20disparity%20is%20sticky%20and%20while%20there%20is%20a%20jobs%20crisis%20also%20for%20unskilled%20labour%2C%20proportionately%20there%20are%20far%20fewer%20jobs%20for%20the%20better%20educated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fstagnant-job-rate-worse-for-the-educated-iim-study%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20launches%20own-brand%20shoes%20after%20fraud%20fine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708238368000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F30C7%2Fproduction%2F_132678421_trumo.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68329886%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ex-president%20promoted%20gold-coloured%20shoes%20priced%20at%20%24399%20at%20a%20sneaker%20convention%20in%20Philadelphia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A188