20she%20decided%20to%20step%20away%20from%20the%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Milda%20Mitkute%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20second-hand%20shopping%20app%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvinted-united-wardrobe-acquisition-secondhand-fashion-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EVinted%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVinted%20created%20me%20as%20a%20person%2C%20and%20as%20a%20professional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20my%20early%20twenties%20and%20had%20just%20moved%20to%20Vilnius%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Lithuania%2C%20to%20complete%20a%20master's%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20apartment%20I%20was%20moving%20into%20came%20with%20a%20much%20smaller%20closet%20than%20I%20had%20at%20my%20mum's%20house.%20I%20couldn't%20take%20all%20my%20clothes%20and%20as%20I%20was%20going%20through%20them%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20had%20more%20than%20100%20items%20that%20still%20had%20labels%20on%20or%20I'd%20only%20worn%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20this%20selfish%20goal%20of%20getting%20rid%20of%20my%20stuff%20and%20was%20also%20curious%20to%20browse%20other%20girls'%20closets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20selfish%20goals%20help%20to%20create%20big%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20completely%20organic%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20chance%2C%20a%20few%20days%20later%20I%20was%20at%20a%20house%20party%20and%20I%20met%20Justas%20Janauskas%2C%20who%20was%20a%20developer.%20It%20was%202%20a.m.%20but%20we%20started%20talking%20about%20this%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20let's%20meet%20in%20a%20few%20days%20and%20think%20about%20the%20name%2C%20about%20action%20planning%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20we%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20of%20us%20had%20any%20business%20experience%2C%20but%20we%20worked%20out%20a%20plan%20to%20launch%20the%20site.%20%26quot%3BGive%20me%20two%20weeks%20to%20design%20a%20site%2C%26quot%3B%20Justus%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20came%20back%20to%20me%20in%2010%20days%20and%20said%20he'd%20done%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20pictures%20of%20my%20clothes%20and%20uploaded%20them%20on%20the%20weekend.%20We%20emailed%20friends%20asking%20them%20to%20add%20items%20so%20that%20we%20could%20make%20the%20catalog%20bigger%20for%20the%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20have%20money%20for%20marketing%2C%20but%20some%20of%20my%20friends%20had%20studied%20journalism%20and%20I%20guess%20it%20must%20have%20reached%20media%20contacts%20because%20within%20a%20few%20hours%20of%20that%20email%20going%20out%20radio%20stations%20and%20newspapers%20started%20to%20call%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20that%20party%20the%20first%20version%20had%20launched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEuropean%20expansion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20three%20years%2C%20we%20were%20both%20still%20working%20in%20normal%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20completing%20my%20master's%20in%20culture%20management%20and%20working%20at%20a%20PR%20agency%2C%20and%20Justus%20was%20an%20IT%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20cost%20we%20had%20was%20paying%20for%20the%20servers.%20It%20was%2010%20euros%20(about%20%2410.80)%20a%20month%20and%20we'd%20track%20it%20on%20an%20Excel%20sheet.%20But%20when%20you%20have%2030%2C000%20people%20on%20your%20site%20you%20need%20more%20servers%20and%20those%20invoices%20started%20going%20up%20to%20200%20euros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20only%20earning%20500%20euros%20a%20month%2C%20so%20that%20was%20a%20fifth%20of%20my%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22llustration%20picture%20shows%20the%20second%20hand%20sales%20app%20'Vinted'%2C%20in%20Charleroi%2C%20Tuesday%2007%20December%202021.%20Vinted%20is%20a%20online%20marketplace%20app%2C%20developed%20in%20Lithuania.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf2b04a610a9069d59aca3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVinted%20has%20about%2075%20million%20users%20worldwide.%20%3Cp%3EVIRGINIE%20LEFOUR%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20adding%20advertising%20on%20the%20site%20to%20cover%20the%20costs%20and%20then%20created%20an%20entity.%20That's%20how%20we%20became%20a%20self-sustainable%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20macro%20analysis%2C%20no%20budgets%2C%20nothing.%20But%20we%20were%20booming.%20By%202011%2C%20we%20were%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic%20and%20Germany%2C%20and%20growing%2060%25%20or%2070%25%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETop%20companies%20in%20Lithuania%20started%20offering%20to%20buy%20us%2C%20but%20we%20rejected%20all%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20this%20platform%20was%20our%20passion%20and%20we%20didn't%20want%20to%20lose%20that%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20our%20first%20business%20%26quot%3Bangel%2C%26quot%3B%20Mantas%20Mikuckas%2C%20joined%20Vinted.%20He%20was%20the%20one%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3Blet's%20try%20and%20spread%20this%20movement%20all%20around%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20expanded%20the%20team%2C%20focused%20on%20design%20usability%2C%20and%20developed%20the%20app%2C%20which%20was%20a%20game%20changer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Accel%20Partners%2C%20the%20guys%20who%20invested%20in%20Facebook%20and%20Spotify%2C%20said%20they'd%20fly%20out%20to%20meet%20us%20immediately.%20They%20put%20in%20%245%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20students%20who%20had%20just%20been%20handed%20all%20that%20money%2C%20but%20we%20used%20that%20moment%20to%20really%20identify%20what%20we%20were%20as%20a%20company%20%E2%80%94%20secondhand%20clothing%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20are%20more%20similar%20than%20we%20are%20different%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20thought%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-secondhand-shopping-luxury-high-end-preloved-items-report-2023-4%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAnd%2520it%2527s%2520not%2520just%2520Gen%2Cover%25202021%252C%2520the%2520report%2520says.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20secondhand%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20post-Soviet%20Union%20concept%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20didn't%20have%20money%2C%20you%20go%20and%20buy%20somewhere%20else%20%E2%80%94%20and%20didn't%20expect%20that%20other%20markets%20might%20be%20interested%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20we%20asked%20girls%20in%20Germany%2C%20France%2C%20and%20the%20US%20why%20they%20used%20Vinted%2C%20it%20was%20all%20about%20selling%20to%20earn%20some%20extra%20cash%2C%20authenticity%2C%20finding%20unique%20clothes%2C%20and%20consuming%20more%20sustainably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Secondhand%20clothes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf3c48a610a9069d59ae7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20secondhand%20clothing%20market%20is%20booming.%3Cp%3EJonas%20Gratzer%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20us%2C%20it%20was%20an%20eye-opener.%20Our%20business%20could%20be%20successful%20across%20borders%20with%20this%20internet-native%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20it%20would%20have%20helped%20to%20do%20more%20research%20about%20the%20competition.%20But%20in%20some%20cases%20when%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20challenge%20you're%20up%20against%2C%20you%20just%20don't%20have%20to%20fear%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20life%20divided%20into%20projects%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20young%20you%20think%20that%20the%20more%20you%20work%2C%20the%20more%20you're%20going%20to%20create.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20that's%20true%20but%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20you%20just%20get%20exhausted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20social%20life.%20I%20would%20go%20into%20the%20office%20every%20morning%20at%206%20a.m.%20and%20not%20leave%20until%2010%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20I%20would%20do%20lots%20of%20things%20differently.%20I'm%2038%20and%20I%20have%20much%20more%20experience.%20I%20know%20how%20to%20create%20balance.%20It's%20not%20only%20about%20business.%20Everyone%20has%20other%20sides%20as%20well%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20their%20character%20to%20explore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Milda%20Mitkute%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ce4108f533b039a884024c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMilda%20Mitkute.%3Cp%3EMalvina%20Stankute%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20I%20turned%2030%2C%20I%20decided%20that%20it%20was%20time%20to%20pause%20the%20Vinted%20project%20and%20start%20a%20family%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20quit%20our%20professional%20lives%20to%20be%20there%20full-time%20for%20our%20children.%20I%20won't%20lie%2C%20we%20did%20have%20a%20babysitter%20to%20help%2C%20but%20we%20wanted%20our%20children%20to%20remember%20that%20we%20weren't%20exhausted%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20seven%20years%2C%20I%20have%20four%20kids.%20I've%20also%20used%20the%20time%20for%20personal%20development%20and%20completed%20two%20more%20master's%20degrees.%20It's%20been%20so%20important%20to%20just%20hear%20the%20thoughts%20in%20my%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I'm%20closing%20the%20family%20project%20and%20developing%20a%20small%20edtech%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20shop%20on%20Vinted%20and%20my%20kids%20use%20it%20too.%20We%20have%20a%20rule%3A%20if%20you%20want%20to%20earn%20pocket%20money%2C%20resell%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMitkute%20stepped%20down%20as%20CEO%20in%202017%20and%20is%20no%20longer%20on%20the%20board%20but%20remains%20a%20shareholder.%20Vinted%20was%20last%20valued%20at%20about%20%243.8%20billion.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20hr